MBER\n\nComment on:\n\nThere have been recurrent rumors since last July that the Burmese were trying to obtain arms from Czechoslovakia.\n\nBurma is in the market for substantial quantities of arms for both its army and police. The army is in the initial phase of a reorganization which will eventually put it on a divisional basis in anticipation of its ultimate relief from pacification duties in order to concentrate on national defense. The police are being prepared to take over the primary responsibility for expanded internal security.\n\nThe Burmese have been promised $10,000,000 worth of American military equipment at favorable prices, and an American survey team is now in Rangoon studying the requirements of the police", "token_count": 128, "token_end_0based": 127, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "8 burma to send arms mission to czechoslovakia in early december comment on there have been recurrent rumors since last july that the burmese were trying to obtain arms from czechoslovakia burma is in the market for substantial quantities of arms for both its army and police the army is in the initial phase of a reorganization which will eventually put it on a divisional basis in anticipation of its ultimate relief from pacification duties in order to concentrate on national defense the police are being prepared to take over the primary responsibility for expanded internal security the burmese have been promised 10 000 000 worth of american military equipment at favorable prices and an american survey team is now in rangoon studying the requirements of the police", "unred_source_page": 13}
